    "body": "### Problem\n\nPresume the binding `vim.keymap.set('n', '<space>e', '<cmd>lua vim.diagnostic.setloclist({severity=\"error\"})<CR>', bufopts)`\r\n\r\nThen open a buffer with LSP attached and some diagnostic messages and record a macro: `qq<space>e<CR>q`\r\n\r\nInvoking this macro freezes neovim. I bumped into this while defining a macro to correct the same error which appeared on several lines (imagine something like a missing semicolon).\r\n\r\nIt seems to be independent of the specific language server. Happens with clangd and ruff (python server).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nabove\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nno freeze\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.1 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1723675123\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno lsp in vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.6.46-1-lts SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst v0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color \n\n### Installation\n\npacman",
